headline: Deckers’s (NYSE:DECK) Q1 Sales Beat Estimates But Stock Drops 13%
summary: Footwear and apparel conglomerate Deckers (NYSE:DECK) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 6.5% year on year to $1.02 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $900 million was less impressive, coming in 2.1% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1 per share was 65.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Deckers Outdoor scraps annual forecast on tariff worries, shares fall
summary: President Donald Trump's trade policy has rattled global markets and has forced several apparel makers to pull or lower their targets for the year as profitability takes a hit from tariffs on key manufacturing partners.  The U.S. is Deckers' largest market by revenue and the company sources about 20% of its products from China.  Deckers would look at some price hikes in the U.S. and negotiate sharing incremental costs due to tariffs with factories to soften the hit from the trade policy, executives said on a post-earnings call.

headline: Deckers Brands Appoints Cynthia L. Davis as Chair of the Board
summary: GOLETA, Calif., May 22, 2025--Deckers Brands (NYSE: DECK), a global leader in designing, marketing, and distributing innovative footwear, apparel, and accessories, today announced the appointment of Cynthia (Cindy) L. Davis as Chair of the Board of Directors (the "Board"), effective immediately. She succeeds Michael (Mike) F. Devine, III, who is retiring from the Board after over 14 years of service, including six years as Chair.
